T~L~165~-675~0~#000000~Courier New~9pt~undefined~undefined~~comment~Works with the following Galaksija Plus ROM images by PVV:
 
- GALAXY_ROM16_v8_6.BIN (16k), alt. GALAXY_v8_6.BIN (64k)
- GALAXY_CHGRGENP.BIN (8k), alt. GALAXY _CHRGEN.BIN (64k)
 
Hardware memory map:
 
  $0000...$0FFF  ROM "A" or "1" – 4 KB contains bootstrap
  $1000...$1FFF  ROM "B" or "2" – 4 KB (optional)
  $2000...$27FF  Keyboard and latch
  $2800...$BFFF  RAM: 30 KB ($2800...$2BFF Video RAM)
  $C000...$C7FF  RAM: 2 KB (SDOS)
  $C800...$CFFF  SD interface
  $D000...$DFFF  Unused, reserved
  $E000...$FFFF  ROM "3" + "4": 8 KB (Graphics, SDOS etc)~1~start~gge616~0~pinpart

T~L~165~-795~0~#000000~Courier New~9pt~undefined~undefined~~comment~Based on PVV's Galaksija Plus clone from 2017. Mods:
 
- integrated audio interface
- address decoder with ATF16V8B
- integrated micro SD socket with level shifters
- NMI reset circuit
- hybrid TH/SMD PCB (SMD discrete components on the bottom side)
- keyboard stackable on the back side (100x300mm)~1~start~gge784~0~pinpart

T~L~165~-370~0~#000000~Courier New~9pt~undefined~undefined~~comment~Soldering sequence:
 
  1. start with the SMD components on the bottom side
     (the SMD components are 0805+ and easy to solder)
  2. solder the SMD components on the top side
  3. mount the IC sockets
  4. mount the rest of the components~1~start~gge808~0~pinpart

T~L~1295~-335~0~#000000~Courier New~~~~~comment~field ADDR = [A15..13]
UPPER6K = A11 # A12

 ...

ROM  = Q0 # Q7

KEY  = Q1 & !UPPER6K
CSSD = Q6 & UPPER6K
A13R = Q6 $ A13
A14R = Q6 $ A14
